# RSS.com safety

## Draft-only workflow

- Episodes are always created as **drafts** for manual review in the RSS.com dashboard
- Never call API endpoints that publish episodes live to Apple Podcasts, Spotify, etc.
- Never use DELETE endpoints

## Warnings

- Warn if `description.md` exceeds 4000 characters (RSS.com limit)
- Warn if `explicit: true` but episode content does not appear explicit (or vice versa)

## Allowed operations

- Upload audio via presigned URL
- Create episode draft with metadata
- Poll processing status (transcode, transcribe)
- Get and update transcript (corrections only)

## User guidance on errors

Explain API and file errors in plain English with a specific fix action. Point to the RSS.com dashboard when credentials or settings are wrong.
